
precompilation:
---------------

escrow   1:   LEX: «Escrow».

escrow   3:   "«Payer»" is a person.
escrow   4:   "«Payee»" is a person.
escrow   5:   "«Arbiter»" is a person.
escrow   6:   "«Fee»" is an amount.

escrow   8:   The «Payer» pays an amount into escrow, appoints the «Payee», appoints the «Arbiter», and fixes the «Fee».

escrow  10:   CLAUSE: «Pay Out».
escrow  11:   The «Arbiter» may pay from escrow the «Fee» to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the «Payee».

escrow  13:   CLAUSE: «Pay Back».
escrow  14:   The «Arbiter» may pay from escrow the «Fee» to themselves, and afterwards return the remainder of the escrow to the «Payer».


